<div id="review_4075041457" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4075041457" />
    <a title="Audrina Gan" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/136825317-audrina-gan"><img alt="Audrina Gan" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_50x66-632230dc9882b4352d753eedf9396530.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4075041457?book_show_action=true">Jun 23, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Audrina Gan" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Audrina Gan" href="/user/show/136825317-audrina-gan">Audrina Gan</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4075041457" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2930797820262182092">I enjoyed this medical thriller. It gave me a better understanding of medicine and also taught us how to look at things from different perspectives and how we shouldn’t judge something by face value. Too much of anything whether it’s gd or bad is not necessarily a good thing. And when we set out to do something, we need to constantly review the original intention of why we do it. </span>

          </span>
        </div>


